Cell[TextData[{
 "c) Write a function ",
 StyleBox["findWord[letterRect, word]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " which is given a letterRect and a single word. The function checks all \
starting locations for the word. The function returns a list containing the \
results from checking all locations in the letterRect for the word. An empty \
list is returned if the word was not found at all. \n\nThe result of the \
second example has two elements, that means there were two starting locations \
where it was found. The first element is {{1,2}, {{0,1}}}. The first element \
is the starting location and the second is the list of directions. So here \
there is only one direction: moving right. The second element is {{4,5}, \
{{-1, 0}, {1,0}}} which reports that from starting position {4,5} the word \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]re\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] was found twice one going \
down and one going to the left."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.632662415822576*^9, {3.6326666952766137`*^9, 3.6326666963266134`*^9}, 
   3.758399647608204*^9, 3.758400277353224*^9, {3.7584004976118217`*^9, 
   3.7584005359230127`*^9}, 3.758425924904293*^9, {3.75842661597182*^9, 
   3.7584266504197903`*^9}, {3.7584799894229155`*^9, 
   3.7584801720401754`*^9}, {3.758486171876472*^9, 3.758486171984483*^9}, {
   3.7585000645591106`*^9, 
   3.758500064646116*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ec88dea1-382f-447c-8da1-\
a814e1acc8ff"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"findWord", "[", 
  RowBox[{"letterRect", ",", " ", "\"\<CPS\>\""}], "]"}]], "Input",
